name: Dollar General

comment: The bathrooms are locked for whatever reason. Just ask for the key. If they give you the wrong one, I’m sure they’ll give you the other one if you ask. Overall, this bathroom might not be a great choice, due to that, but it’s better than a lot of other places, I think.

name: Cloverleaf Antique, Vintage, And Collectibles
directions: Both Bathrooms located In the back. One stall for each.
comment: Both ‘men’s’ and ‘women’s’ bathroom are often mistaken together since they’re very causal and in a quirky atmosphere. No one’s ever paying attention and it’s hard to notice there’s even a difference between both bathrooms (the only thing indicating a ‘men’s’ bathroom is a painting of a man smiling, but they are menstrual products in the ‘men’s’ bathroom) the bathrooms are not formal at all and very free and open, contrary to most public bathrooms.  The atmosphere is very calm and comfortable so really no one pays attention or notices. One stall. I would consider both bathrooms unisex. I felt really comfortable to use any room I wanted, and I saw many people mistake the ‘men’s’ bathroom as just a unisex bathroom.
